                <h1>Unraveling Madness: The Yellow Wallpaper Film</h1>
                <p>The "Yellow Wallpaper" film adapts Charlotte Perkins Gilman's classic story of mental illness and female oppression. It follows the protagonist's descent into madness as she becomes obsessed with the patterns in her room's wallpaper, symbolizing her struggles for freedom and self-identity. A haunting exploration of societal expectations.</p>
